HEADWORD: Spiodea
<hw>Spi*o"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
<ets>Spio</ets> the typical genus.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
extensive division of marine Annelida, including those that are without
oral tentacles or cirri, and have the gills, when present, mostly
arranged along the sides of the body. They generally live in burrows or
tubes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirable</ent>⟦br⟧
